<MELItem itemNbr="27-58-01" id="X-BOEING:FTID:81205.787.DDG.CU.MEL.2-27-58-01.1.2-27-58-01">
<Title>Flap Position/Skew Sensors</Title>
<DispatchCondition repairInterval="C" nbrInstalled="24" nbrRequired="10">
<DispatchConditionRemarks>
<Para>One sensor per sensor pair and all inboard flap position sensors may be inoperative provided:</Para>
<List listType="a.">
<ListItem>
<Para>Slat position sensors operate normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
<ListItem>
<Para>Spoiler actuator systems operate normally.</Para>
</ListItem>
</List>
</DispatchConditionRemarks>
<DispatchProcedure>
<MaintenanceNote>
<Para>Failure of both sensors of an inboard flap position sensor pair will cause loss of the trailing edge variable camber (cruise flaps) function.  The CRUISE FLAPS FAULT status message will be displayed.  The airplane must also be dispatched using MEL item 27-51-02.</Para>
<Para>If desired, flap position and skew sensor indications may be reviewed on the FLAP/SLAT maintenance page.</Para>
</MaintenanceNote>
</DispatchProcedure>
</DispatchCondition>
</MELItem>
